properties.areaDesc: Admiralty Inlet Area; Western Whatcom County
properties.headline: Coastal Flood Advisory issued January 10 at 4:02PM PST until January 11 at 10:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Minor coastal flooding expected.

* WHERE...Western Whatcom County and Admiralty Inlet Area.

* WHEN...From 4 AM to 10 AM PST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Flooding of lots, parks, and roads with only
isolated road closures expected.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The combination of high astronomical tide
and low pressure will result in minor tidal overflows on
Saturday near Port Townsend and Cherry Point. High tide at Port
Townsend is around 6:00 AM PST at 9.5 feet. The tidal anomaly is
0.5 to 1.0 foot. High tide at Cherry Point is around 7:00 AM PST
at 10.3 feet. The tidal anomaly is 0.5 to 0.8 foot.
properties.instruction:
If travel is required, allow extra time as some roads may be
closed. Do not drive around barricades or through water of
unknown depth. Take the necessary actions to protect flood-prone
property.

NWSheadline: COASTAL FLOOD ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 4 AM TO 10 AM PST SATURDAY
